The Eastern Cape department of health has been instructed by the Bhisho legislature to sack Dr Mthandeki Xamlashe as the senior manager of medical services of the province, as his appointment “does not comply with necessary provisions for recruitment”. But the department has hit back, saying it is not going to happen. According to a portfolio committee report adopted by the legislature last Thursday, the department, in appointing the man known as “Mr Fix It”, did not fulfil the requirement for open competition in filling a vacant, funded post and therefore the appointment should be reversed because it did not comply with the department’s recruitment policy. The report was adopted by the legislature. For the full story get a copy of the Dispatch or subscribe to our e-Edition for the complete newspaper with jobs, classifieds, crosswords, TV schedules and back editions.